{"id": "page-00040", "type": "page_text", "source_file": "asm-handbook-v2.pdf", "page": 40, "text": "For 2xx.x though 8xx.x alloys, the alloy group is determined\nby the alloying element present in the greatest mean\npercentage, except in cases in which the composition being\nregistered qualifies as a modification of a previously\nAluminum, ‡ 99.00% 1xx.x registered alloy. If the greatest mean percentage is common\nto more than one alloying element, the alloy group is\ndetermined by the element that comes first in the sequence.\nAluminum alloys grouped by major alloying element(s): 2xx.x\nCopper The second two digits identify the specific aluminum alloy\nor, for the aluminum (1 xx.x) series, indicate purity. The last\ndigit, which is separated from the others by a decimal point,\nSilicon, with added copper and/or magnesium 3xx.x indicates the product form, whether casting or ingot. A\nmodification of an original alloy, or of the impurity limits for\nunalloyed aluminum, is indicated by a serial letter preceding\nSilicon 4xx.x\nthe numerical designation. The serial letters are assigned in\nalphabetical sequence starting with A but omitting I, O, Q,\nand X, the X being reserved for experimental alloys. Explicit\nMagnesium 5xx.x\nrules have been established for determining whether a\nproposed composition is a modification of an existing alloy\nZinc 7xx.x\nor if it is a new alloy.\nAluminum Castings and Ingot. For the 1xx.x group, the\nTin 8xx.x second two of the four digits in the designation indicate the\nminimum aluminum percentage. These digits are the same as\nthe two digits to the right of the decimal point in the\nOther elements 9xx.x minimum aluminum percentage when expressed to the\nnearest 0.01%. The last digit indicates the product form:\n1xx.0 indicates castings, and 1xx.1 indicates ingot.\nUnused series 6xx.x\nAluminum Alloy Castings and Ingot. For the 2 xx.x\nthrough 9xx.x alloy groups, the second two of the four digits in the designation have no special significance but serve only\nto identify the different alloys in the group. The last digit, which is to the right of the decimal point, indicates the product\nform: xxx.0 indicates castings, and xxx.1 indicates ingot having limits for alloying elements the same as those for the alloy\nin the form of castings, except for those listed in Table 1.\nTable 1 Alloying element and impurity specifications for ingots that will be remelted into sand, permanent\nmold, and die castings\nAlloying element Composition, wt%\nCasting Ingot\nSand and permanent mold Die All\nIron £ 0.15 . . . . . . Casting -0.03\n>0.15-0.25 . . . . . . Casting -0.05\n>0.25-0.6 . . . . . . Casting -0.10\n>0.6-1.0 . . . . . . Casting -0.2", "has_tables": true, "num_tables": 2, "metadata": {}}
