{"id": "page-00105", "type": "page_text", "source_file": "asm-handbook-v2.pdf", "page": 105, "text": "(b) Per ISO standard No. R115 unless other standard (R164, R2147, or 3522) specified.\n(c) D, die casting; P, permanent mold; s, sand. Other products may pertain to the composition shown even though not listed.\n(d) The Al content for unalloyed aluminum by remelt is the difference between 100.00% and the sum of all other metallic elements present\nin amounts of 0.010% or more each, expressed to the second decimal before determining the sum.\n(e) (Mn + Cr + Ti + V) = 0.0 25% max.\n(f) Fe/Si ratio 2.5 min.\n(g) Fe/Si ratio 2.0 min.\n(h) Fe/Si ratio 1.5 min.\n(i) 0.40 to 1.0% Ag.\n(j) 0.50-1.0% Ag.\n(k) Ti + Zr = 0.50 max.\n(l) 0.20 to 0.30% Sb; 0.20 to 0.30% Co; 0.10 to 0.30% Zr.\n(m) 0.05-0.15% V; 0.10-0.25% Zr.\n(n) 0.06-0.20% V.", "has_tables": false, "num_tables": 0, "metadata": {}}
