or nickel decreasing ductility and\nresistance to corrosion. Increasing magnesium reduces ductility.\nApplications\nTypical uses. Cooking utensils, food-handling equipment, marine fittings, miscellaneous thin-section castings. Die\ncastings: applications where good pressure tightness, above-average ductility, and excellent resistance to corrosion are", "has_tables": false, "num_tables": 0, "metadata": {}}
